OL,3,C'Some things I witnessed, no human
OL,4,Cshould have to live with'
OL,6,FMr Skelton said he could not even boil
OL,7,Fan egg and his wife, who he described
OL,8,Fas a "homebird", did everything for
OL,9,Fhim.
OL,11,FHe said his wife had welcomed a
OL,12,FRomanian orphan into their home in
OL,13,F1997, an act he described as "pure
OL,14,Fkindness".
OL,16,FFollowing his wife's death, Mr Skelton
OL,17,Fmaintained the family's link to the
OL,18,Fcharity and he eventually married the
OL,19,Fmother of a Romanian girl who had
OL,20,Fstayed at his home.
