OL,3,C'Some things I witnessed, no human
OL,4,Cshould have to live with'
OL,6,FMr Skelton said: "My whole focus
OL,7,Fturned to looking for my daughter
OL,8,Fbecause I thought my daughter was
OL,9,Fburied underneath her mammy.
OL,11,F"When you start digging, some of the
OL,12,Fthings I witnessed, that no human
OL,13,Fbeing should have to live with.
OL,15,F"I was there in the wrong place at the
OL,16,Fwrong time. It was just horrendous.
OL,18,F"There are things that stays with me,
OL,19,Fthe smell of burning flesh, I can't
OL,20,Fget that out of my head, the cries of
OL,21,Fpeople."
